Key Findings
Kebumen Regency recorded the highest poverty rate in Central Java at 17.59%.
Wonosobo and Brebes also experienced relatively high poverty rates.
Semarang City had the lowest poverty rate at 4.34%.
Salatiga City and Kudus Regency were among the regions with the lowest poverty levels.
The average poverty rate in Central Java was 11.01%.
Significant differences exist between regions with the highest and lowest poverty rates, indicating socioeconomic disparities across the province.

Conclusion:
The analysis shows that poverty levels in Central Java varied considerably across regencies and cities in 2020. Kebumen, Wonosobo, and Brebes were identified as the regions with the highest poverty rates, while Semarang City, Salatiga City, and Kudus Regency recorded the lowest rates.
These findings highlight the importance of equitable economic development and targeted poverty alleviation programs to reduce regional disparities and improve social welfare throughout Central Java.

